*TiddlyWiki is an open source single page application wiki. A single HTML file contains CSS, JavaScript, and the content. The content is divided into a series of sections, or Tiddlers. A user is encouraged to read a TiddlyWiki by following links rather than sequentially scrolling down the page.

== How to get it ==

*To get a TiddlyWiki go to this page. http://www.tiddlywiki.com 
*You can also right click on this link and save an empty TiddlyWiki to your computer to get started
http://www.tiddlywiki.com/beta/empty.html

==Setup==

*Click on the empty.html file it will open in your default browser
*Firefox works best due to javascript needing to run.
*It works great on usb drives and with DropBox


== TiddlyWiki Glass==

*I use a version of TiddlyWiki named TiddlyWiki Glass
*You Can get it here http://dl.getdropbox.com/u/55061/TWGlass2_00.zip

*Just right click to download the zip file.
*Extract to a location of your choice.
*Click the TWGlass.html File and it will open in your default browser.
*Firefox works best due to javascript needing to run. 
*It works great on usb drives and with DropBox)
* Here is a link to an online demo of TiddlyWiki Glass http://glass.tiddlyspot.com/